. , http://EarthInteractions.org, [Available online at]; Oki, T., Nishimura, T., Dirmeyer, P., Assessment of annual runoff from land surface models using Total Runoff Integrating Pathways (TRIP) (1999) J. Meteor. Soc. Japan, 77, pp. 235-255; Oki, T., Agata, Y., Kanae, S., Saruhashi, T., Musiake, K., Global water resources assessment under climatic change in 2050 using TRIP (2003), 280, pp. 124-133. , IAHS PublPalmer, T.N., Branković, Č., Richardson, D.S., A probability and decision-model analysis of PROVST seasonal multi-model ensemble integration (2000) Quart. J. Roy. Meteor. Soc., 126, pp. 2012-2033; Peterson, B.J., Holmes, R.M., McClelland, J.W., Vörösmarty, C.J., Lammers, R.B., Shiklomanov, A.I., Shiklomanov, I.A., Rahmstorf, S., Increasing river discharge to the Arctic Ocean (2002) Science, 298, pp. 2171-2173; Seckler, D., Barker, R., Amarasinghe, U., Water scarcity in the twenty-first century (1999) Water Resour. Dev., 15, pp. 29-42; Vörösmarty, C.J., Green, P., Salisbury, J., Lammers, R.B., Global water resources: Vulnerability from climate change and population growth (2000) Science, 289, pp. 284-288; Wu, P., Wood, R., Stott, P., Human influence on increasing Arctic river discharges (2005) Geophys. Res. Lett., 32. , L02703, doi:10.1029/2004GLO21570","Kitoh, A.; Climate Research Department, Meteorological Research Institute, 1-1 Nagamine, Tsukuba, Ibaraki 305-0052, Japan; email: kitoh@mri-jma.go.jp",,,,,,,,1525755X,,,,"English","J. Hydrometeorol.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-33750936559
